{"TopicId":40921,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Lifting Bodies","CreatedByName":"NinpoFox","CreatedById":58957,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-04T03:46:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NinpoFox","CreatedById":58957,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-04T03:46:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EJust wondering if anyone else is experimenting with lifting bodies like the old X-24. Here\u0027s my first test.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/eaFVOIy\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/eaFVOIy.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022eaFVOIy.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/wzQZuYF\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/wzQZuYF.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022wzQZuYF.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/tL2uhFz\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/tL2uhFz.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022tL2uhFz.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/C7wUGsL\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/C7wUGsL.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022C7wUGsL.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/Iw5UiRw\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Iw5UiRw.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022Iw5UiRw.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI put the center of lift slightly forward of the center of gravity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt floats like a leaf in the wind.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMy next step is to take it to my space station and return.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NinpoFox","CreatedById":58957,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-04T16:12:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHeading to my station now.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/YHhigcs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/YHhigcs.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022YHhigcs.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/ltYLI66\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ltYLI66.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022ltYLI66.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/esAICCc\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/esAICCc.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022esAICCc.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/jOyX8Ur\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/jOyX8Ur.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022jOyX8Ur.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyHook","CreatedById":31496,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-04T17:06:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have been experimenting with lifting bodies, and I wish that support for it were implemented in the game. The trick for implementing it would be tricky though, as the only solution I can thing of entails cfg editing fuselages to be wings as well. This would bring about some balance issues though. I\u0027m off to theorycraft how that might work!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"espm400","CreatedById":71109,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-04T18:15:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFerram Aerospace Research supports lifting body and blended wing aircraft (used to use a Dyna-Soarer-style crew vehicle). If you\u0027re interested in those type of aircraft, I would suggest getting that mod.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SDIR","CreatedById":59117,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-05T03:56:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027d be nice to not only have lifting bodies for planes, but also for capsules like in real life.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arq","CreatedById":71084,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-05T05:21:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAfter reading this thread I had a fun time spending an hour just building planes around a single SRB, launching them up, then gliding them back down to the runway. Kind of like the Natter \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bachem_Ba_349\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bachem_Ba_349\u003C/a\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"espm400","CreatedById":71109,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-05T05:53:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022arq\u0022 data-cite=\u0022arq\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EAfter reading this thread I had a fun time spending an hour just building planes around a single SRB, launching them up, then gliding them back down to the runway. Kind of like the Natter \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bachem_Ba_349\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bachem_Ba_349\u003C/a\u003E.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat\u0027s a lot closer to a missile than a lifting body. Lifting bodies are aircraft where the body itself creates most of the lift (see:\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lifting_body\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELifting Body\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI do believe that I incorrectly classified the \u0027Dyan-Soarer\u0027 as a blended wing body, though, as it\u0027s probably closer to a conventional aircraft than a BWB. My bad...\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SDIR\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SDIR\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIt\u0027d be nice to not only have lifting bodies for planes, but also for capsules like in real life.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m currently learning Blender and intend to release some classic lifting body designs (as I said, I\u0027m just starting out, so don\u0027t expect anything anytime soon)...\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-08-05T05:57:07Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2013 05:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by espm400\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NinpoFox","CreatedById":58957,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-20T01:58:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EStill playing with this idea. These end up be more like rocket assist gliders than lifting bodies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/S4gm52p\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/S4gm52p.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022S4gm52p.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/EZfQqes\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/EZfQqes.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022EZfQqes.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/nuOlsgx\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/nuOlsgx.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022nuOlsgx.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m creating more lift by attaching an extra set of wings on the fuselage at a lower location than the first and them rotating the new wings to \u0022blend\u0022 them into the first.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DisarmingBaton5","CreatedById":68576,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-20T03:13:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHow do you guys overcome the stability issues? I find that when trying to mount a spaceplane on a rocket, the wings cause the rocket to become extremely unstable.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Giggleplex777","CreatedById":29829,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-20T03:42:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/idH2CLm.png\u0022 alt=\u0022idH2CLm.png\u0022\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-20T04:17:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/64324284@N05/9144879530/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7428/9144879530_27e18af5c1_c.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00229144879530_27e18af5c1_c.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWorks until you want to land... FAR is not terribly forgiving.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NinpoFox","CreatedById":58957,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-08-25T02:57:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThis is my second \u0022lifting body.\u0022 I flew it to my space station and returned. Stability was an issue at launch and I had to stay \u0022on top\u0022 of the nav ball to make it go straight up. At just over 10K altitude it calmed down and I leaned it over to 90 to set up rendezvous.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/eZw4UQK\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/eZw4UQK.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022eZw4UQK.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/H237PU7\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/H237PU7.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022H237PU7.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/LyaLL0a\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/LyaLL0a.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022LyaLL0a.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/oK6fz9w\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/oK6fz9w.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022oK6fz9w.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/BjjdnOh\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/BjjdnOh.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022BjjdnOh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/mjdyZRS\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mjdyZRS.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mjdyZRS.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELots of fun to fly. Needs to be trimmed up a little to maintain level flight.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}